<div class="container px-4 py-3 my-3 text-center">
  <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-body-emphasis">Pricing</h1>
  <h2>Pay for what gives you value: Data Mart attributes</h2>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-6 mx-auto">
      <p class="lead mb-4">
        Flexible pricing that focuses on your Return On Investment.
      </p>
      <div class="d-grid gap-2 d-sm-flex justify-content-sm-center">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-4 gap-3" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#modal-contact-us">Contact us</button>
      </div>
      <div class="d-grid gap-2 d-sm-flex justify-content-sm-center mt-3">
        <a class="icon-link" href="https://aws.amazon.com/marketplace/pp/prodview-irz3tf6c7owr4" target="_blank">Show Yotilla in the AWS Marketplace <i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right"></i></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{% macro pricePackage(tier='Tier', price='20.000€', dma='500', pricePerDMA='4,17€', instances='1' ) %}
<div class="col">
  <div class="card mb-4 rounded-3 shadow-sm">
    <div class="card-header py-3">
      <h4 class="my-0 fw-normal">{{ tier }}</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <h1 class="card-title pricing-card-title">{{price}} <small class="text-body-secondary fw-light fs-6">/month</small></h1>
      <ul class="list-unstyled mt-3 mb-4">
        <li>{{dma}} Data Mart attributes</li>
        <li><small>{{instances}} Yotilla Instance(s)</small></li>
        <li><small>{{pricePerDMA}} / additional Data Mart attribute</small></li>
        <li><small>Unlimited seats / users</small></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

<div class="container px-4 py-3 text-center">
  <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-3 row-cols-lg-4">

    {{pricePackage('Small', '2.080€', '500', '4,17€', '1')}}
    {{pricePackage('Medium', '3.750€', '1.000', '3,75€', '1')}}
    {{pricePackage('Large', '6.250€', '2.000', '3,13€', '2')}}
    {{pricePackage('X-Large', '8.330€', '3.500', '2,38€', '3')}}

  </div>
</div>

<div class="container px-4 py-3">
  <h2 class="border-bottom mb-3">Return on Investment calculator</h2>

  <form id="roi-calculator">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col">
          <h3 class="fs-4 text-body-emphasis">Size of your Data Warehouse</h3>
          <div class="mb-3">
            <label for="data-mart-attributes" class="form-label">How many Data Mart attributes?</label>
            <input type="number" class="form-control" id="data-mart-attributes" aria-describedby="dataMartAttributeHelp" value="1200">
            <div id="dataMartAttributeHelp" class="form-text">A Data Mart attribute (e.g. Product Price) is only counted once if it's part of several facts or dimensions.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="mb-3">
            <label for="data-mart-attributes" class="form-label">How many Data Engineers?</label>
            <input type="number" class="form-control" id="data-mart-attributes" aria-describedby="dataMartAttributeHelp" value="3">
            <div id="dataMartAttributeHelp" class="form-text">How many Data Engineers are involved building the Data Warehouse.</div>
          </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h3 class="fs-4 text-body-emphasis">Cost comparison</h3>
        <div class="mb-3">
          <label for="select-yotilla-tier" class="form-label">Yotilla Tier</label>
          <select class="form-select" aria-label="Yotilla Tier select" id="select-yotilla-tier">
            <option value="small">Small</option>
            <option value="medium" selected>Medium</option>
            <option value="large">Large</option>
            <option value="x-large">X-Large</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Costs per month: 3.750€</li>
          <li>Cost savings: 58%</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</form>

<div class="container px-4 py-3">
  <h2 class="border-bottom mb-3">Metering</h2>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">
      <p>
        The unit in which consumption is measured is the total number of deployed Data Mart attributes per month.
        The number of deployed Data Mart attributes for an Yotilla instance per month is the maximum of deployed Data Mart attributes over all environments (e.g., development and production) of the Yotilla instance per month.
        The total number of deployed Data Mart attributes is the sum of deployed Data Mart attributes over all instances per month.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each package includes a fixed number of deployed Data Mart attributes. Metering of the additional deployed Data Mart attributes takes place when the number of deployed Data Mart attributes exceeds the number of included deployed Data Mart attributes.
      </p>
      <p>
        In addition, each package includes a fixed number of Yotilla instances. Metering of the additional Yotilla instances only takes place when the number of started Yotilla instances exceeds the number of included Yotilla instances.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>